<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<Defs>

    <ThingDef Name="OCARINA_MantledBeastsMantleBase" ParentName="ApparelBase" Abstract="True">
        <tickerType>Normal</tickerType>
        <uiIconScale>1.4</uiIconScale>
        <thingCategories>
            <li>ArmorHeadgear</li>
        </thingCategories>
        <tradeTags>
            <li>Clothing</li>
            <li>Armor</li>
            <li>OCARINA_ApparelMantle</li>
        </tradeTags>
        <apparel>
            <countsAsClothingForNudity>false</countsAsClothingForNudity>
            <developmentalStageFilter>Child, Adult</developmentalStageFilter>
            <bodyPartGroups>
                <li>UpperHead</li>
            </bodyPartGroups>
            <layers>
                <li>Overhead</li>
            </layers>
            <tags>
                <li>OCARINA_ApparelMantle</li>
            </tags>
            <drawData>
                <dataNorth>
                    <layer>-3</layer>
                </dataNorth>
            </drawData>
            <parentTagDef>ApparelHead</parentTagDef>
        </apparel>
        <modExtensions>
            <li Class="MantledBeasts.DefModExtension_ClothingRestriction">
                <requiredGenesToEquip>
                    <li>OCARINA_MantledBeastsFur</li>
                </requiredGenesToEquip>
            </li>
        </modExtensions>
        <colorGenerator Class="ColorGenerator_StandardApparel" />
    </ThingDef>


    <ThingDef ParentName="OCARINA_MantledBeastsMantleBase">
        <defName>OCARINA_Apparel_AegisciteMantle</defName>
        <label>aegiscite visor</label>
        <description>A wearable visor made specifically for the Va'ji (other xenotypes cannot wear these visors), the aegiscite visor is common among inhabitants of Aegis, with them being rarer as one strays further from known sources of aegiscite. This is the highest tier of visor that can be crafted.\n\nVisors are important parts of Va'ji society, much like clothing is to other xenotypes. Va'ji prefer to wear their visors for most of their lives, as they function not only as fashion and individual expression, but as utility to help improve their poor eyesight and improve communication.</description>
        <techLevel>Ultra</techLevel>
        <thingClass>MantledBeasts.Apparel_MoodTexture</thingClass>
        <graphicData>
            <texPath>Things/Pawn/Humanlike/Apparel/AegisciteMantle/AegisciteMantle</texPath>
            <graphicClass>Graphic_Single</graphicClass>
        </graphicData>
        <statBases>
            <WorkToMake>8000</WorkToMake>
            <MaxHitPoints>120</MaxHitPoints>
            <Mass>0.2</Mass>
            <ArmorRating_Sharp>1.00</ArmorRating_Sharp>
            <ArmorRating_Blunt>0.46</ArmorRating_Blunt>
            <ArmorRating_Heat>0.55</ArmorRating_Heat>
            <Insulation_Cold>1</Insulation_Cold>
            <EquipDelay>1.5</EquipDelay>
        </statBases>
        <equippedStatOffsets>
            <GlobalLearningFactor>0.2</GlobalLearningFactor>
            <WorkSpeedGlobal>0.2</WorkSpeedGlobal>
            <ResearchSpeed>0.2</ResearchSpeed>
            <GeneralLaborSpeed>0.2</GeneralLaborSpeed>
            <MedicalSurgerySuccessChance>0.2</MedicalSurgerySuccessChance>
            <NegotiationAbility>0.2</NegotiationAbility>
            <SocialImpact>0.2</SocialImpact>
        </equippedStatOffsets>
        <recipeMaker>
            <researchPrerequisite>AdvancedFabrication</researchPrerequisite>
            <recipeUsers>
                <li>FabricationBench</li>
            </recipeUsers>
            <skillRequirements>
                <Crafting>6</Crafting>
            </skillRequirements>
            <workSkill>Crafting</workSkill>
            <displayPriority>999</displayPriority>
            <workSpeedStat>GeneralLaborSpeed</workSpeedStat>
            <effectWorking>Smith</effectWorking>
            <soundWorking>Recipe_Smith</soundWorking>
            <unfinishedThingDef>UnfinishedArmor</unfinishedThingDef>
        </recipeMaker>
        <costList>
            <OCARINA_Aegiscite>30</OCARINA_Aegiscite>
            <ComponentSpacer>1</ComponentSpacer>
        </costList>
        <apparel>
            <wornGraphicPath>Things/Pawn/Humanlike/Apparel/AegisciteMantle/AegisciteMantle</wornGraphicPath>
        </apparel>
        <comps>
            <li Class="VEF.Apparels.CompProperties_ApparelHediffs">
                <hediffDefnames>
                    <li>OCARINA_AegisciteMantleHediff</li>
                </hediffDefnames>
            </li>
        </comps>
    </ThingDef>

    <ThingDef ParentName="OCARINA_MantledBeastsMantleBase">
        <defName>OCARINA_Apparel_IndustrialMantle</defName>
        <label>industrial visor</label>
        <description>A wearable visor made specifically for the Va'ji (other xenotypes cannot wear these visors), this visor is is much more industrial in terms of quality compared to aegiscite visors one may find elsewhere. Still, an improvement to the Va'jis' natural limitations. \n\nVisors are important parts of Va'ji society, much like clothing is to other xenotypes. Va'ji prefer to wear their visors for most of their lives, as they function not only as fashion and individual expression, but as utility to help improve their poor eyesight and improve communication.</description>
        <techLevel>Industrial</techLevel>
        <thingClass>MantledBeasts.Apparel_MoodTexture</thingClass>
        <graphicData>
            <texPath>Things/Pawn/Humanlike/Apparel/IndustrialMantle/IndustrialMantle</texPath>
            <graphicClass>Graphic_Single</graphicClass>
        </graphicData>
        <statBases>
            <WorkToMake>3200</WorkToMake>
            <MaxHitPoints>100</MaxHitPoints>
            <Mass>0.5</Mass>
            <StuffEffectMultiplierArmor>0.42</StuffEffectMultiplierArmor>
            <StuffEffectMultiplierInsulation_Cold>0.22</StuffEffectMultiplierInsulation_Cold>
            <StuffEffectMultiplierInsulation_Heat>0</StuffEffectMultiplierInsulation_Heat>
            <EquipDelay>1.67</EquipDelay>
        </statBases>
        <equippedStatOffsets>
            <GlobalLearningFactor>0.05</GlobalLearningFactor>
            <WorkSpeedGlobal>0.05</WorkSpeedGlobal>
            <GeneralLaborSpeed>0.05</GeneralLaborSpeed>
            <SocialImpact>0.15</SocialImpact>
        </equippedStatOffsets>
        <recipeMaker>
            <researchPrerequisite>Machining</researchPrerequisite>
            <recipeUsers>
                <li>TableMachining</li>
            </recipeUsers>
            <skillRequirements>
                <Crafting>3</Crafting>
            </skillRequirements>
            <workSkill>Crafting</workSkill>
            <displayPriority>999</displayPriority>
            <workSpeedStat>GeneralLaborSpeed</workSpeedStat>
            <effectWorking>Smith</effectWorking>
            <soundWorking>Recipe_Smith</soundWorking>
            <unfinishedThingDef>UnfinishedArmor</unfinishedThingDef>
        </recipeMaker>
        <apparel>
            <wornGraphicPath>Things/Pawn/Humanlike/Apparel/IndustrialMantle/IndustrialMantle</wornGraphicPath>
        </apparel>
        <stuffCategories>
            <li>Metallic</li>
        </stuffCategories>
        <costStuffCount>30</costStuffCount>
        <costList>
            <ComponentIndustrial>1</ComponentIndustrial>
        </costList>
    </ThingDef>

    <ThingDef ParentName="OCARINA_MantledBeastsMantleBase">
        <defName>OCARINA_Apparel_TribalMantle</defName>
        <label>visormask</label>
        <description>A wearable mask made specifically for the Va'ji (other xenotypes cannot wear these masks), this mask is a facsimilie of a visor, being completely techless. Va'ji can still sometimes carve patterns into their own masks to fulfill their internal self-expression desires. Being nothing more than a piece of fancy wood, the visormask doesn't provide any of the major stat benefits the other mantles do.\n\nVisors are important parts of Va'ji society, much like clothing is to other xenotypes. Va'ji prefer to wear their visors for most of their lives, as they function as fashion and individual expression.</description>
        <techLevel>Neolithic</techLevel>
        <graphicData>
            <texPath>Things/Pawn/Humanlike/Apparel/TribalMantle/TribalMantle</texPath>
            <graphicClass>Graphic_Single</graphicClass>
        </graphicData>
        <statBases>
            <WorkToMake>1280</WorkToMake>
            <MaxHitPoints>100</MaxHitPoints>
            <Mass>0.8</Mass>
            <StuffEffectMultiplierArmor>0.22</StuffEffectMultiplierArmor>
            <StuffEffectMultiplierInsulation_Cold>0.03</StuffEffectMultiplierInsulation_Cold>
            <StuffEffectMultiplierInsulation_Heat>0</StuffEffectMultiplierInsulation_Heat>
            <EquipDelay>1.8</EquipDelay>
        </statBases>
        <equippedStatOffsets>
            <SocialImpact>0.2</SocialImpact>
            <PainShockThreshold>0.1</PainShockThreshold>
        </equippedStatOffsets>
        <recipeMaker>
            <recipeUsers>
                <li>CraftingSpot</li>
            </recipeUsers>
            <workSkill>Crafting</workSkill>
            <displayPriority>999</displayPriority>
            <workSpeedStat>GeneralLaborSpeed</workSpeedStat>
            <effectWorking>Smith</effectWorking>
            <soundWorking>Recipe_Smith</soundWorking>
            <unfinishedThingDef>UnfinishedArmor</unfinishedThingDef>
        </recipeMaker>
        <apparel>
            <wornGraphicPath>Things/Pawn/Humanlike/Apparel/TribalMantle/TribalMantle</wornGraphicPath>
        </apparel>
        <stuffCategories>
            <li>Woody</li>
        </stuffCategories>
        <costStuffCount>30</costStuffCount>
    </ThingDef>

</Defs>